text.tspan: - Your final design needs to be on the "Print" layer
- Convert all text to Paths by clicking on Path > Object to Path (Ctrl + Shift + C)
- Images must be in vector format. You can use Path > Trace Bitmap to convert
- The "Key Grids" layer is for reference only. You can print all the way to the edge of the
frame. However, since there is a +/-0.01" tolerance, we suggest that you stay within the
- All print objects must be black. Non-printed areas must be transparent.
- Make sure file is saved as "Inkscape SVG" file type.
- Use the Layers Menu to hide and show preset layouts (Ctrl + Shift + L)
- Get additional symbols and graphics from the "Artwork" layer
- (Ctrl + Alt + V) to paste in the same position
- Hold Ctrl while dragging to keep object on the same axis
- Turn on snapping to help with aligning
- Ctrl + Scroll Wheel to Zoom In/Out
- Hold down Scroll Wheel to pan with mouse
- Press "4" to zoom to fit to screen
- Use the online designer to configure your keycap color scheme.
